"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"1. The boss's goal for the employees must be clear, deepen and detailed as much as possible. If you are too busy, give it to your assistant to deepen and refine, and then check it yourself and plan it out.\\n2. When the goal is set, a meeting should be held with the executive to specify when to start and when to end. We must completely put an end to the habit of not making clear decisions after a meeting! Decided, there is a habit of inaction.\\n3. Oneself must also actively participate in the execution of the task and promote the project.\\n4. To assume the responsibility of a leader, you can do nothing, but you must grasp an accurate direction forward, and provide employees with help all the time to help them solve the problems they encounter. Actively provide the resources they need.\\n\\nIf they have any questions, they will answer and solve them in a timely manner.\\n\\n1. If the energy permits, you must take the lead, play the role of an example, roll up your sleeves and do it yourself. If you donâ€™t do it yourself, you must choose the responsible person, and let the responsible person play the list on your behalf.\\n\\nEntrepreneur Business School Serving Entrepreneurs 195\\n\\nKind of role.\\n\\n1. To be clear about what employees need, instead of thinking about what goals they want to achieve. We promise that employees will be rewarded for their good work. Give them a reason for execution.\\n2. Performance appraisal, people who do well must be rewarded in time. Those who do poorly must be punished promptly. Leading troops to fight, rewards and punishments must be good tools.\\n\\nBasically, without using all of these 7 items, the execution ability of employees can be improved.\",\"timestamp\":1634801728,\"title\":\"How to improve the executive ability of enterprise employees\"},\"digest\":\"pIOXjPAJ6eL5VK2euIdS1vyOrG-ijS0KV5GOC9Tq4-Y\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x0500e3b6f7b1214a11851b9B348020C08018403b\",\"signingKey\":\"